The paper discusses an algorithm for solving nonconvex optimization problems in a distributed and asynchronous manner. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), distributed computing (cs.DC), dynamical systems (cs.DS), control systems (cs.SY), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Among these, machine learning and distributed computing seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on solving optimization problems using a distributed and asynchronous approach.
